# Copy to .env (git-ignored) and fill in. NEVER commit the real values.
#
# The org runs on GitHub-native primitives (DESIGN.md): work is Issues + the org Project,
# wakes come from scripts/runner.py, and `gh` supplies all GitHub credentials —
# authenticate once with `gh auth login` (plus `gh auth refresh -s project` for the
# Project board). No chat server, no bot tokens; agent cycles run through the Claude Code
# SDK on the Chairman's plan (agent-run.sh), so there is no per-agent API key here either.

# The GitHub repos the runner polls (wake-rules.yaml routes their events).
ORG_GH_REPO={{ORG_GH_REPO}}
PRODUCT_GH_REPO={{PRODUCT_GH_REPO}}

# Path to the org source of truth and the agent definitions (defaults shown).
ORG_CHART_PATH=./org-chart.yaml
AGENTS_DIR=./agents

# The org Project (board). github-pm-setup.sh creates it with this title; pm-gh.sh and
# warden.py find it by title, or by number when org-chart.yaml pins pm_project_number.
# PM_PROJECT_TITLE=Org Project

# The local clone of the product repo (where IT works and opens PRs; never prod-merges).
PRODUCT_REPO=

# The runner: shadow = poll + log the would-be wakes without waking anyone (the default —
# boot in shadow first and read the log); live = actually wake departments off GitHub
# events (agent-run.sh guards — .halt, locking, metering — still apply).
RUNNER_MODE=shadow

# Org-wide spend breaker (DESIGN.md invariant 3): when today's metered cost in
# state/spend.jsonl reaches this many dollars, the runner holds every wake until the
# ledger rolls over. Per-department envelopes live in org-chart.yaml.
# SPEND_BREAKER_DAILY_USD=25

# Demand telemetry, if/when you wire it (metrics.yaml sources).
# GUMROAD_ACCESS_TOKEN=...
# REPORTS_API_URL=...
